            <para>For helium the energy minimum at point X is not low enough that the two atoms stay together and so they move apart again. This is why when we draw the Lewis diagram for helium we draw one helium atom on its own. There is no bond.</para>
            <para>We also see that helium already has a full outermost energy level and so no compound forms.</para>
